{"editorCode":"    ;  The escalator\r\n;\r\n;Albin wants to compute the height of a 2-floor escalator located in a mall. The escalator has two parts and connects the ground floor to the second floor of the mall. The only information he has access to is the lengths c1 and c2 of each part of the escalator, as well as the angle t of the slope of the escalator formed with the horizontal ground.\r\n;He started making the procedure \"two_floor_escalator\" in order to calculate its total height, but he faces some difficulties. Can you help him?\r\n;----------------        -------------\r\n;For further instructions click on the papyrus button.\r\n;----------------        -------------\r\n\r\n;Procedures\r\n;...........\r\n\r\n;Task 1\r\n;...............\r\n\r\nTO two_floor_escalator :b1 :b2 :c1 :c2 :t1 :t2\r\nstarting_point\r\nescalator :b1 :c1 :t1\r\ntransposition2 :c2 :t2\r\nescalator :b2 :c2 :t2\r\nend\r\n\r\nclean\r\ntwo_floor_escalator 20 50 150 120 30 45\r\n;----------------------\r\n\r\nto transposition2 :c :t2\r\npu rt 90 fd :c*cos(:t2) lt 90 fd :c*sin(:t2) pd\r\nend\r\n\r\nclean\r\ntransposition2 120 45 \r\n;---------------\r\nto escalator :b :c :t\r\ntransposition :b :c :t\r\nstairs :c :t\r\nend\r\n\r\nclean\r\nescalator  30 40 30\r\n\r\n;Task 2\r\n;..............\r\nto two_floor_escalator2 :c1 :c2 :t1 :t2\r\nstarting_point\r\nescalator :c1 :t1\r\ntransposition2 :c2 :t2\r\nescalator :c2 :t2\r\nprint 'height of the two floor escalator:'\r\nprint .............\r\nend\r\n\r\n\r\nclean\r\ntwo_floor_escalator2 20 50 150 120 30 45\r\n\r\n;Task 3\r\n;...............\r\nTo three_floor_escalator :c1 :c2 :c3 :t1 :t2 :t3\r\ntwo_floor_escalator :c1 :c2 :t1 :t2\r\n..................\r\n.....................\r\nprint 'height of the three floor escalator:'\r\nprint ................\r\nend\r\n\r\n\r\nclean\r\nthree_floor_escalator ... ... ... ... ... ... \r\n;==========================\r\n;==========================\r\nto transposition :b :c :t \r\nblue\r\nbk :b lt 90 fd :c*cos(:t)\r\nrt 180-:t fd :c\r\npu bk :c lt 90-:t pd\r\nblack\r\nend\r\n\r\ntransposition 50 60 50\r\n;--------------------\r\n;---------------------\r\nto stairs :c :t \r\nrepeat 10 [step :c :t]\r\nend\r\n\r\nstairs 60 70\r\n\r\n;---------------------\r\n\r\nTo step :c :t \r\nfd :c/10*sin(:t) rt 90 \r\nfd :c/10*cos(:t) lt 90\r\nend\r\n\r\n;----------------------\r\n\r\nto black \r\nsetpencolor [0 0 0]\r\nend\r\n\r\nto blue\r\nsetpencolor [0 0 255]\r\nend\r\n\r\nto starting_point\r\npu setxy -50 0 pd\r\nend\r\n\r\nstarting_point\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n","hiddenCode":[],"sceneCode":"","cameraPos":{"x":0,"y":1.2246467991473532e-14,"z":200},"character":"Bird","notes":"\t\t\t\tThe escalator\n\t\t*************************\n\nTASK 1\n.............................\n   Run the command \"two_floor_escalator 20  50  150  120  30  45\".\n\n   •    What does the avatar construct? \n\n  Now run the sub-procedures \"escalator\" and \"transposition2\" in order to locate where the problem is.\n\nActivate the variation tool and explore:\n\n   •    What is the role of each variable? \n   •    Which variable defines the height of each floor?\n\n  Albin knows that:\n                      c1=150, :c2=120, :t1=30 and :t2= 45. \n\n   •   Find the values of the variables b1 and :b2 for which the 2-floor escalator is formed correctly. \nTry many values for the variables using the variation tool.\nCompose a conjecture and then test it.\n\nTASK 2\n.............................\n1. Correct the procedure two_floor_escalator in order for the escalator to always be formed correctly (for any possible value of the variables :c and :t). Then update the sub-procedures called in the procedure.\n\n\n2. Complete the procedure \"two_floor_escalator2\" with the command \"print\" in order to print the height of the two floors. \n\nTASK 3\n................................\n Can you complete the procedure \"three_floor_escalator\" properly in order for the avatar to construct a three-floor escalator and, also, print its total height? \n  \n\n\n\n\n  \t\t\t\t-----------------\n\t\t\t\t       TIP\n\t\t\t\t-----------------\nTASK 2\n.............................\n   The relation that connects the side :b with the angle :t and the hypotenuses :c is:\n \n\t\t\t\t\t:b = :c*sin(:t)\nTASK 3\n................................\n   The first two floors are constructed by the procedure \"two_floor_escalator\". All you miss is the 3rd floor.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","sliders":{},"objects":[]}